<p align="center">\
  <img src="assets/logo.svg" alt="Luna Agent" width="120" height="120">\
</p>\
\
<h1 align="center">Luna Agent</h1>\
\
<p align="center">\
  A custom minimal AI agent with persistent memory, MCP tool integration, Discord interface, and structured observability.<br>\
  Runs entirely on local hardware \'97 no cloud API costs.\
</p>\
\
<p align="center">\
  <a href="https://github.com/nonatofabio/luna-agent/actions/workflows/tests.yml"><img src="https://github.com/nonatofabio/luna-agent/actions/workflows/tests.yml/badge.svg" alt="Tests"></a>\
  <a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg" alt="License: MIT"></a>\
  <a href="https://www.python.org/downloads/"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.11+-blue.svg" alt="Python 3.11+"></a>\
</p>\
\
---\
\
~2300 lines of Python. No frameworks.\
\
## Why Custom\
\
We evaluated existing agent frameworks and rejected them all:\
\
- **OpenClaw**: 400K lines of code, 42K exposed instances on Shodan. Too large to audit, too large to trust.\
- **ZeroClaw**: 9 days old at time of evaluation. Too immature.\
- **NanoClaw**: Too thin \'97 would need to rebuild most of it anyway.\
\
The core needs (memory, tools, chat, logging) are individually well-solved problems. No 400K-line framework needed.\
\
## Architecture\
\
```\
Discord (discord.py)\
     |\
     v\
+-----------------------+\
|    Luna Agent Core    |\
|                       |\
|  agent.py             |  agent loop: msg \uc0\u8594  memory \u8594  prompt \u8594  LLM \u8594  tools \u8594  respond\
|    \uc0\u9500 \u9472 \u9472  llm.py         |  single LLM client, any OpenAI-compatible endpoint\
|    \uc0\u9500 \u9472 \u9472  memory.py      |  SQLite + FTS5 + sqlite-vec hybrid search\
|    \uc0\u9500 \u9472 \u9472  tools.py       |  native tools: bash, files, web fetch, web search\
|    \uc0\u9500 \u9472 \u9472  tool_output.py |  smart output pipeline for large results\
|    \uc0\u9500 \u9472 \u9472  mcp_manager.py |  MCP client for community tool servers\
|    \uc0\u9492 \u9472 \u9472  observe.py     |  structured JSON logging\
|                       |\
+-----------------------+\
         |\
         v\
   any OpenAI-compatible    llama-server, Ollama, vLLM, cloud APIs, etc.\
   endpoint\
```\
\
All LLM traffic flows through a single `LLMClient` with a configurable endpoint URL. Point it at `localhost:8001` for llama-server, or any other OpenAI-compatible endpoint. To insert an AI firewall later, change the URL \'97 zero code changes required.\
\
**Thinking model support:** Luna handles reasoning models (Qwen3.5, etc.) automatically \'97 extracting `reasoning_content`, falling back to cleaned reasoning when content is empty, and stripping leaked markup (`<thinking>`, `<tool_call>`, etc.) from output.\
\
## Quick Start\
\
```bash\
git clone https://github.com/nonatofabio/luna-agent.git\
cd luna-agent\
python3 -m venv .venv\
source .venv/bin/activate\
pip install -e ".[dev]"\
\
# Configure MCP servers (optional)\
cp mcp_servers.example.json mcp_servers.json\
\
# Run tests\
pytest tests/ -v\
\
# Run without Discord (headless mode)\
python -m luna\
\
# Run with Discord\
DISCORD_TOKEN=your-token-here python -m luna\
```\
\
