# Security Policy\
\
## Reporting a Vulnerability\
\
Please report security vulnerabilities through [GitHub's private vulnerability reporting](https://github.com/nonatofabio/luna-agent/security/advisories/new).\
\
**Do not** open a public issue for security vulnerabilities.\
\
## Scope\
\
Security issues we care about:\
\
- **Sandbox escapes** \'97 bypassing bash command blocklist or workspace write restrictions\
- **Prompt injection** \'97 manipulating the agent through tool output or memory content\
- **Memory poisoning** \'97 corrupting the memory database through crafted inputs\
- **MCP server exploitation** \'97 using MCP tool calls to access unintended resources\
\
## Out of Scope\
\
- Denial of service against the local LLM server\
- Issues requiring physical access to the host machine\
- Social engineering attacks against Discord users\
\
## Response\
\
We aim to acknowledge reports within 48 hours and provide a fix or mitigation within 7 days for confirmed vulnerabilities.\
\
\
